{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Born to Springfield's mercantile gentry, 1764","body":"She was born 13 December 1764 to Col. Josiah Dwight — Yale 1736, owner of an iron foundry, a potash manufactory, and 5,000 acres of Hampshire County land — and to Elizabeth Buckminster of Brookfield. Her father died in 1768 leaving an estate worth £9,458 when she was four; her mother survived to 1798."},{"number":2,"category":"marriage","header":"Married Judge John Hooker, December 1790","body":"On 18 December 1790 in Springfield she married John Hooker, Yale 1782 graduate and son of the Rev. John of Northampton. She bore him ten children between 1791 and 1808, including Dr. Worthington Hooker (H01407) and Elizabeth Dwight Hooker Packard (H01403)."}],"slug":"sarah-dwight-1764"},"H00264":{"id":"H00264","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":5,"compiler_ancestor":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1729,"month":3,"day":19,"city":"Kensington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1777,"month":2,"day":6,"city":"Northampton","county":"Hampshire","state":"Massachusetts","country":"United States","cause":"smallpox"},"parents":{"father_id":"H00098","mother_id":"I00041"},"tags":["compiler_ancestor","yale_graduate","clergy","minister","epidemic_death"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 264"}],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I00043","children_ids":["H00524","H00525","H00526","H00527","H00528","H00529","H00530","H00531","H00532"],"marriage_number":1,"end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1777,"date_year":1755,"date_month":12,"date_day":10,"location_country":"United States"}],"compiler_ancestor":true,"ministry_positions":[{"role":"Minister","location":"Northampton, Massachusetts","dates":"1753-1777","duration_years":2